<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="33" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="33">
This genus with 18 species (
<bibRefCitation pageId="6" pageNumber="33">ThripsWiki 2013</bibRefCitation>
) is included in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Anaphothrips" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Anaphothrips" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Anaphothrips</taxonomicName>
genus-group (
<bibRefCitation author="Mound, LA" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="14" pageNumber="41" pagination="1 - 76" title="Australian Thripinae of the Anaphothrips genus-group (Thysanoptera), with three new genera and thirty-three new species." volume="2042" year="2009">Mound and Masumoto 2009</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Bhatti et al. (2003)</bibRefCitation>
published a catalogue of the 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Eremiothrips" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eremiothrips" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Eremiothrips</taxonomicName>
in Iran with key for separating the nine species of this genus. Recognition of species of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Eremiothrips" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eremiothrips" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Eremiothrips</taxonomicName>
based on females is extremely difficult, since the general appearance and fine structural details of females are very similar in related species. However, males can be assigned readily to species because of distinctive structural features (
<bibRefCitation pageId="6" pageNumber="33">Bhatti et al. 2003</bibRefCitation>
). In Iran, the genus includes 12 species (
<bibRefCitation author="Bhatti, JS" journalOrPublisher="Thrips" pageId="13" pageNumber="40" pagination="1 - 23" title="Eremiothrips zurstrasseni, new species, from Khuzestan province in Iran (Insecta: Terebrantia: Thripidae)." volume="10" year="2009 b">Bhatti et al. 2009b</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ramezani, L" journalOrPublisher="Thrips" pageId="15" pageNumber="42" pagination="1 - 18" title="Discovery of Eremiothrips similis in Iran, with a catalogue of species of Eremiothrips in Iran (Insecta: Terebrantia: Thripidae)." volume="11" year="2009">Ramezani et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Minaei, K" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="13" pageNumber="40" pagination="56 - 62" title="The genus Eremiothrips (Thysanoptera: Thripidae) in Iran, with one new species." volume="3349" year="2012 a">Minaei 2012a</bibRefCitation>
) and a key to Iranian 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Eremiothrips" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Eremiothrips" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Eremiothrips</taxonomicName>
based on the male sex is available (
<bibRefCitation author="Minaei, K" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="13" pageNumber="40" pagination="56 - 62" title="The genus Eremiothrips (Thysanoptera: Thripidae) in Iran, with one new species." volume="3349" year="2012 a">Minaei 2012a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
